<br>
The word &quot;feminazi&quot; (feminist Nazi), it does nothing for your arguments, aside from flagging you as a dyed-in-the-wool Rush Limbaugh automoton who was exposed heavily to his ramblings in your (continuing) emotional adolescence.  People who survive politically on granting equal pay, better scholarships, or more political freedom to women bear next to no resemblance to the Nazi party, who were bent on annihilating (yes, that's with death involved,) all the &quot;unpleasant&quot; facets of society. <br>
<br>
Your words about women make it sound as if you've never known a real woman in your life; you have this mythical image in your mind of a snide, sexy, ambitious, condescending, wheedling, power-hungry female legal intern or something, just out of college, consciously and maliciously using her sexuality and the public sentiment for gender equality in the workplace to gain an unfair advantage over men in the workplace.  And you know, most people, that's most of America, just want to get an honest job and work for a living, and earn enough to pay rent, bills, and buy enough food.<br>
<br>
You call yourself a redneck, which to me smacks of low-income, back-woods living in a too-small abode with 4 generations of immediate family, or maybe that's 'hillbilly,' I can't keep them straight.  I bet you've never known a day of hardship in your life.  I'll bet your mother never had to work two jobs and support three children because your father was dead since your age 3.  <br>
<br>
You keep insisting on referring to women by their sex organs.  Every single sentence you type about women adds to the impression that you consider yourself, personally, to be better than, smarter than, more capable than every single woman ever born.  For all your feigned political shrewdness and social awareness, you don't have any idea about the nature of healthy human interaction, aside from what you see in the media.<br>
<br>
You talk about annexing Afghanistan, because we spent so much money on the war there.  You talk about death and domination so casually, I wonder if you'd feel so lofty and in control, if you had to point an M-16 at someone and squeeze the trigger.  Even when they're pointing firearms right back at you, and you must do it, I imagine it's not an easy thing.<br>
<br>
I'll bet you think that women and queers fighting in the military is a horrible, silly idea, inspired by romantic notions of equality and feeling left-out?  Tell me why an average, healthy, straight, patriotic 18 year old male would volunteer for active infantry duty?  Love of country?  Desire to prove oneself?  Who really cares why he wants to, but he won't be told no, that's for certain.  Consider that a young woman wants the same thing, for the same reasons, do you believe it?  Do you assume she's just trying to make a political statement, to prove 'you have to let me on your team, teacher says...'  What you pretend to know about the motivations of such a woman speaks volumes about your politics.<br>
<br>
Go ahead and respond to each word of each phrase above with all your cunning.  Debunk everything I've said and implied.  Use the word 'ridiculous' and 'bleeding-heart' lots too, by all means.  Fact remains, you're out of touch with everything you claim to have neatly sewn-up answers to.<br>
