<br>
Barbera Olsen (R.I.P.)<br>
Anne Coulter. Writer, lawyer, editorial personality, conservative, fiesty, cute, married..<br>
<br>
I think Kate Mulgrew, whom I bashed in an earlier message, is a pretty nifty person. She's just got a screwed-up value system, IMO. <br>
<br>
Angelika Lleopardbait. This is a weird one, I know. But I always look foreward to talking to her. I'm fairly confident she's a woman in real life, and she's about the only female character in the game I bother watching my manners with. Much.<br>
<br>
Nancy Reagan; I like her mostly for her almost obssessive devotion to the President. Beyond that... eh. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Gillian Anderson has the world's best figure and a smile that lights up the world... and we'd get along for about 37 seconds... <br>
<br>
Peggy Noonan... some of the words behind Reagan's speeches.<br>
<br>
Mel Gibson's wife. I've never seen her, don't even know her name, but any woman that can stay married to one of the most wanted men on the planet, and keep him fidelitous, has my respect. <br>
<br>
There are more women I know personally and like, but their names would mean nothing, so there's not much point in listing them.<br>
There are also other celebrity/well-known females on the list but I'm tired and have things I've been neglecting that I need to do now.<br>
